{"timestamp":1784782892804,"user":"crouton.ai@gmail.com","action":{"kind":"comment","text":"Add full-diff pages beside review, navigated with r and d.\n\nReview and diff are now parallel page families: plural list pages (reviews, diffs) and singular per-file pages (review, diff). Review pages show what is left for you to read; diff pages show the whole base..tip diff, blind to review state. r and d enter a family from the show page or a home row, and swap a list or per-file page for its counterpart in the other family — the one place a 'Nothing left to review.' page is expected is swapping to review from a diff you have already cleared. Stepping (^/$) walks review pages along the files left and diff pages along every changed file; a diff render records the file as displayed, so a later mark does not ask.\n\nThe all-in-one review-diffs buffer (page kind 'diffs', cabaret.reviewDiffs, previously on d) is dropped, along with the @-bar machinery in the page grammar that existed for it. Both hosts share the same keymap, checked by the counterpart test."}}
